09/04/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The Romanian team leading the EU accession talks in Brussels closed the chapter on free movement of capital on Monday (7 April).
Bucharest hopes to close three other chapters by the end of June, bringing the number of closed chapters to 20 out of 30.
On Tuesday, Romanian Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana wrapped up a visit to France saying that Paris would not consider his country's position on Iraq a barrier to EU accession.
(Mediafax, Rompres - 09/04/03)
